20class RtcEventGenericPacketSent final : public RtcEvent {
21 public:
22 static constexpr Type kType = Type::GenericPacketSent;
23
24 RtcEventGenericPacketSent(int64_t packet_number,
25 size_t overhead_length,
26 size_t payload_length,
27 size_t padding_length);
28 ~RtcEventGenericPacketSent() override;
29
30 std::unique_ptr<RtcEventGenericPacketSent> Copy() const;
31
32 Type GetType() const override { return kType; }
33 bool IsConfigEvent() const override { return false; }
34
35 // An identifier of the packet.
36 int64_t packet_number() const { return packet_number_; }
37
38 // Total packet length, including all packetization overheads, but not
39 // including ICE/TURN/IP overheads.
40 size_t packet_length() const {
41 return overhead_length_ + payload_length_ + padding_length_;
42 }
43
44 // The number of bytes in overhead, including framing overheads, acks if
45 // present, etc.
46 size_t overhead_length() const { return overhead_length_; }
47
48 // Length of payload sent (size of raw audio/video/data), without
49 // packetization overheads. This may still include serialization overheads.
50 size_t payload_length() const { return payload_length_; }
51
52 size_t padding_length() const { return padding_length_; }
53
54 private:
55 RtcEventGenericPacketSent(const RtcEventGenericPacketSent& packet);
56
57 const int64_t packet_number_;
58 const size_t overhead_length_;
59 const size_t payload_length_;
60 const size_t padding_length_;
61};
